conversation.message:
@all: Let’s turn this into a concrete plan so nobody stays blocked on vague “waiting for specs.”

@Lisa: Since your mockups are ready, can you post:
- The exact screens that need backend data  
- For each screen: the data fields you expect (names, types, example values) and key user actions (e.g., “save profile,” “filter list”)  
This will help @Kevin sketch draft API contracts even before final specs are signed off.

@Kevin: While waiting on final specs from @Mike, can you:
- Propose a **draft API contract** (endpoints, request/response shapes, error codes) based on Lisa’s mockups and current user stories  
- Flag any assumptions or open questions right in that doc  
This gives @Mike something concrete to review instead of starting from a blank page, and lets @Lisa start wiring against mock data.

@Mike: We need at least a **v0 API spec** so implementation can begin. Can you:
- Confirm when you can review/approve Kevin’s draft today  
- Or, if it’s faster, schedule a **20–30 min working session today** with @Kevin and @Lisa to lock in the minimal viable set of endpoints and fields  
Even a “good enough for this sprint” version is better than blocking on a perfect spec.

@Nina: Once the draft API and UI flows are outlined, you can:
- Start a **test plan** based on the agreed endpoints and key user flows  
- Note any edge cases or validation rules you need clarified so @Mike and @Kevin can incorporate them early.
